 | A-060 | Sanction submission changes `application_status` and `appraisal_status` to `submitted_to_sanction_committee` but leaves `LoanApplication.current_stage = credit_assessment` until source governance names the corresponding one-of-six SOP stage value. | Source data-model and auth workflow tables name the submitted status but do not name a separate `current_stage` value for sanction; inventing `sanction`, `approval`, or another stage would create a new persisted vocabulary. | `docs/source/data-model.md` loan-application status/§13.1; `docs/source/auth-permissions.md` §20.1; `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §24.5 | 006G and Epic 007 | Medium | Yes | 2026-07-10 | Epic 007 should set a stage only if a source-backed canonical value is added; historical status facts must not be rewritten. |
+| A-061 | Explicitly revalidating a non-draft `legacy_unverified` appraisal must never make an old Credit Manager decision approve newly pinned prerequisite facts. A `review_pending` row may remain pending after revalidation because no terminal review exists; a `reviewed` row must return to draft, clear only its latest-review projection, preserve immutable review history, and require maker resubmission plus a fresh independent review. Rejected/submitted terminal rows remain quarantined until a separately governed repair exists. | ADR-0003 requires conservative provenance and fresh frozen facts, while migration 0005 can downgrade every state but the current repair is draft-only. Preserving a reviewed status after changing its evidence would silently transfer authority to facts the reviewer never saw; reopening is the conservative workflow default. The source does not define a legacy-remediation state machine, so the exception is explicit and reviewable. | `docs/adr/ADR-0003-freeze-appraisal-prerequisite-projections.md`; `docs/adr/ADR-0004-append-only-appraisal-review-decisions.md`; `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §3/§24; `docs/source/data-model.md` §14.4/§34; architecture review `2026-07-10_213352_architecture_review` | 006E4-legacy-appraisal-remediation-and-history-backfill | High | Yes | 2026-07-10 | If governance defines another remediation flow, version the explicit action. Never silently relabel unproven facts, erase immutable review history, or let a pre-remediation review satisfy sanction gating. |
