Architecture review completed successfully. No production code, protected files, or `docs/source/` files were modified.

Key findings:

- Critical: `006F3` was merged despite its packet stating “Failed acceptance; do not commit or merge”—four required PostgreSQL tests were found but none executed. `006G` added a fifth unexecuted PostgreSQL race.
- High: migration `0005` can permanently strand non-draft `legacy_unverified` appraisals and omit a reconstructable returned-review reason.
- High: loaded appraisal responses are sent wholesale on PATCH, so existing and returned drafts include read-only fields and fail strict validation.
- High: the frontend locally reconstructs action/status state, loses the sanction case UUID after reload, and gates revalidation with the wrong authority.
- High: 006H replaced the approved staged workbench composition without screenshot or interaction-test evidence.
- Medium: the credit module directly persists an approvals model, reversing the documented dependency direction.

Corrective work is sequenced as:

`006E4 → 006F4 → 006G2 → 006H2 → 006H3 → 006X`

ADR-0005 assigns sanction-case creation, reads, and future enrichment to one approvals-owned deep module interface.

Validation passed:

- 372 backend tests; five PostgreSQL-only skips
- 93% coverage, above the 85% floor
- Django check and migration sync
- Frontend lint and typecheck
- 126 frontend tests
- Production build
- Diff, state, artifact, and protected-path checks

Full details are in [REVIEW_FINDINGS.md](/Users/amitkallapa/LMS/.ralph/worktrees/2026-07-10_213352_architecture_review/docs/working/REVIEW_FINDINGS.md), [review-packet.md](/Users/amitkallapa/LMS/.ralph/worktrees/2026-07-10_213352_architecture_review/.ralph/runs/2026-07-10_213352_architecture_review/review-packet.md), and [HANDOFF.md](/Users/amitkallapa/LMS/.ralph/worktrees/2026-07-10_213352_architecture_review/docs/working/HANDOFF.md).
